  "last_post_content": "DevOps culture transformation shows what works. Pay attention to this.\n\nUnpopular opinion: building influence as a devops engineer matters more than most realize.\n\nTeams often find that having a strong voice in the development and operations process is crucial for success. The reality is that DevOps engineers with influence can drive meaningful change and improve overall efficiency.\n\n\u2022 Establish a strong understanding of the development and operations pipeline\n\u2022 Develop a data-driven approach to decision making\n\u2022 Build relationships with key stakeholders across teams\n\nCommon mistakes to avoid include trying to exert influence without first building trust and credibility. Evidence suggests that taking the time to understand the needs and concerns of team members is essential.\n\nThe data shows that getting started with building influence takes time and effort, but the payoff can be significant. Production experience shows that even small gains in influence can lead to major improvements in efficiency and productivity.\n\nTimeline expectations vary, but most teams find that building influence is an ongoing process that requires consistent effort over several months.\n\nWhat career advice would you add? Share your experience below.\n\n#finops #sre #devops #cloudengineering #infrastructure",
